**Project:** Automated Disaster Damage Assessment from Aerial Imagery  

---

# 1) Overview

The frontend is responsible for delivering an interactive geospatial dashboard that:

- Displays pre- and post-disaster aerial imagery
- Overlays model-generated damage classifications
- Allows address and street-level querying
- Integrates a chatbot for disaster impact questions
- Provides an intuitive and responsive user experience

The frontend acts as the presentation and interaction layer between users and the Vision-Language Model (VLM) backend system.

---

# 2) Technology Stack

|       Layer       |     Technology    |
|-------------------|-------------------|
| Framework         | React             |
| Mapping Library   | Leaflet           |
| Styling           | Tailwind CSS      |
| State Management  | React Context API |
| API Communication | Axios / Fetch     |
| Deployment        | Vercel / Azure    |

---

