---

# 4) UI Layout Design

## Dashboard Layout Concept

- Interactive Map
- Chatbot Interface

### Key UI Elements

- Toggle switch for pre/post imagery
- Damage classification legend
- Address search bar above the map
- Loading indicators for model responses
- Tooltips on buildings for damage classification

---

# 5) Map & Geospatial Design

## Mapping Library: Leaflet

### Core Features

- Tile-based base map
- Overlay GeoJSON damage data
- Layer toggling for pre/post imagery
- Interactive building-level popups

### Damage Classification Color Scheme

| Damage Level | Color  |
|--------------|--------|
| No Damage    | Green  |
| Minor        | Yellow |
| Major        | Orange |
| Destroyed    | Red    |

### GeoJSON Handling

- Fetch GeoJSON from backend API
- Dynamically apply style based on classification
- Add hover and click interactions
- Optimize performance for large datasets

---

# 6) Chatbot Integration

The chatbot interface will:

- Accept natural language user queries
- Send POST requests to backend `/query` endpoint
- Display structured responses
- Maintain conversation history within the session

### Example

- "How many buildings are severely damaged on Elm Street?"
- "Summarize damage in this neighborhood."
- "What is the damage classification at 123 Main St?"

---

# 7) State Management Plan

Global state will manage:

- Selected imagery layer (pre/post)
- Damage overlay visibility
- Selected building or address
- Chat history
- Loading and error states

React Context API will centralize shared state across components.

---

# 8) API Integration Plan

|   Endpoint     | Method |           Purpose           |
|----------------|--------|-----------------------------|
| `/damage-data` | GET    | Fetch GeoJSON damage data   |
| `/query`       | POST   | Process chatbot queries     |
| `/evaluate`    | GET    | Retrieve evaluation metrics |

All API calls will:

- Include loading indicators
- Handle error responses
- Log failures for debugging

---

# 9) UI/UX Design Goals

- Clean, modern, and professional interface
- Clear visual distinction between damage levels
- Minimal cognitive overload
- Responsive design (desktop-first)
- Smooth map interactions
- Fast perceived performance

